To see the block use this command :
>> lsblk                              #show disk and the partition 

To format the disk use this command :
>> sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/xvdf           

To mount it use the following command :
>> sudo mkdir /data
>> sudo mount /dev/xvdf /data

verify using :
>> df -h 
                                       #shows the disk usage 
To see the UUID of the disk :
>> sudo blkid

Edit the fstab and add the UUID to make the volume persistent even after the reboot

>> sudo vim /etc/fstab  
add :
UUID=the uuid of the volume  /data ext4 defaults,nofail 0 2

To test the fstab :
>> sudo mount -a

To 

To reboot :
>> sudo reboot


Make volume -> format it -> mount it  -> then use it 
if you want to partition the volume partition it before  formatting or else it will be difficult and  you can 
loose the data


